# Process Diagram – SAP Journal Posting Automation

This document presents the **AS-IS (current state)** and **TO-BE (automated state)** process flows for recurring month-end journal postings into SAP.

The analysis focuses on repetitive journal entry requests received from internal teams during the month-end close process.

---

# AS-IS Process (Manual Posting)

## Process Description

During the month-end close period, the finance team receives recurring journal entry requests from internal teams.  
These entries are typically provided in **CSV format** and require **manual posting into SAP**.

The process is repetitive and generates operational workload due to the number of requests received over a short time window.

Typical workload observed:
- ~30 recurring requests
- requests received across ~4 days
- manual SAP posting required for each request

---

## AS-IS Process Flow

### Internal Team
Start  
↓  
Prepare recurring journal entries  
↓  
Export journal entries to CSV file  
↓  
Send CSV file to Finance Analyst via email  

### Finance Analyst
Receive journal entry request  
↓  
Review CSV file structure and posting details  

Decision: **Is the CSV file complete and understandable?**

If NO  
→ Contact Internal Team and request clarification  
→ Updated file received  
→ Review CSV file again  

If YES  
↓  
Log into SAP  
↓  
Manually enter journal entry data  
↓  
Verify posting parameters (accounts, cost centers, amounts)  

Decision: **Is the journal entry correct?**

If NO  
→ Correct manual input  
→ Re-enter journal entry data  

If YES  
↓  
Submit journal entry in SAP  
↓  
Journal entry recorded in SAP  
↓  
Repeat process for next request  

End

---

## AS-IS Pain Points

The manual process creates several operational challenges:

- repetitive manual SAP postings
- high workload during month-end close
- interruptions caused by incoming requests
- increased risk of manual posting errors
- inefficient use of analyst time

---

# TO-BE Process (Automated Posting)

## Process Description

The improved process introduces an **automation bot** capable of reading structured CSV input files and posting recurring journal entries into SAP.

The bot performs validation checks before posting entries and only involves the finance analyst when exceptions occur.

---

## TO-BE Process Flow

### Internal Team
Start  
↓  
Prepare recurring journal entries  
↓  
Export journal entries to CSV file  
↓  
Submit CSV file for automated processing  

---

### Automation Bot / SAP

Bot reads CSV input file  
↓  
Validate file structure and mandatory fields  

Decision: **Is the input file valid?**

If NO  
→ Generate error notification  
→ Send error email to Finance Analyst  

If YES  
↓  
Log into SAP automatically  
↓  
Apply predefined posting logic  
↓  
Submit journal entry into SAP  

Decision: **Was SAP posting successful?**

If NO  
→ Generate error notification  
→ Send error email to Finance Analyst  

If YES  
↓  
Record posting result in log  
↓  
Journal entry posted automatically  

End

---

### Finance Analyst (Exception Handling)

Monitor automated processing results  

If error notification received:

Decision: **Can the CSV file be corrected?**

If YES  
→ Correct CSV file  
→ Resubmit file for automated processing  

If NO  
→ Perform manual journal posting in SAP  

End

---

# Key Improvements

The automated process introduces several operational improvements:

- reduction of repetitive manual work
- fewer interruptions during month-end close
- lower risk of manual input errors
- faster handling of recurring journal postings
- improved use of analyst capacity

The finance analyst becomes involved **only in exception scenarios**, rather than executing the entire process manually.

